The rootcause of this exception is a bug in Hibernate Criteria that generate a wrong SQL query with the same alias for different primary key.
This is a snapshot of the query generated and you can see the alias **ID2_8_** is duplicated for different tables columns. 

    select composite1_.ID_RSK_IND as ID2_8_, dimension8_.MNE_DIM as MNE3_90_4_, 
    roles9_.ID_GRP_DIM as ID1_90_8_, role10_.ID_ROL as ID2_8_

Oracle can handle this situation but hibernate will try to load the entity with a key of the other entity.

As workaround i found that adding `@Fetch(value = FetchMode.SUBSELECT)` will solve this bug I don&#39;t know why but it works.

    @ManyToMany(fetch = FetchType.EAGER)
    @Fetch(value = FetchMode.SUBSELECT)
    private List&lt;Role&gt; roles = new ArrayList&lt;Role&gt;();

